text: Tore Kallstad (born 1 August 1965) is a retired Norwegian footballer. He was born in Lørenskog, and has several matches played for the junior national team of Norway. He played in the Norwegian Premier League in 1986 and 1988 for Strømmen IF, and in 1992 and 1993 for Lillestrøm SK, amassing 57 matches and 14 goals. ==References== Category:1965 births Category:Living people Category:People from Lørenskog Category:Norwegian footballers Category:Strømmen IF players Category:Lillestrøm SK players Category:Eliteserien players Category:Association footballers not categorized by position
